<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="1025" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1058,1410,1461]" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025">
E t y m o l o g y: 
<emphasis box="[359,436,1410,1431]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="1025">Ordinis</emphasis>
is a Latin noun with a meaning of &quot;line&quot;; with reference to the broad testaceous line on the elytral disc. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
